The man that sadly lost his life during a collision with a tanker transporting hazardous materials on Wednesday has still not been identified. The bakkie he was in, collided with a truck on the Stoffberg road near the entrance of Laerskool Uitkyk. According to information, the bakkie driver stopped to avoid a pothole, when the truck which was carrying explosives ploughed into the vehicle. Van Wettenâ€™s Towing Services attended to the scene and safely recovered the truck and its dangerous cargo.